Nigerians In Diaspora Commission (NIDCOM) has condemned the attack on Senator Ike Ekweremadu at the 2nd Annual Igbo Cultural Festival held in Nuremberg, Germany. <img class="size-full wp-image-1241300 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=640%2C896&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="896" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=41%2C58&amp;ssl=1 41w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=139%2C194&amp;ssl=1 139w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=93%2C130&amp;ssl=1 93w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?resize=560%2C784&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ekweremadu.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> In a statement in Abuja the Chairman of NIDCOM, Mrs AbiKe Dabiri-Erewa said that the incident was an embarrassment to the country. “It is also shamefully pathetic that an event, which was nobly put together by the Ndi-Igbo community whose members make up the majority of Nigerians living in Germany, ended up in such a disgraceful manner,” she said. Dabiri-Erewa noted that the event was to provide a forum for the Diasporans and various stakeholders to network and facilitate better cooperation between German and Nigerian businesses. Enweremadu confirmed the attack in a statement released by his Media Assistant, Uche Anichukwu in Abuja Vanguard 